The Supply Officer prepare and maintain Semi-Expendable Property Card, Registry of Semi-Expendable Property Issued and Report of Semi-Expendable Property Issued.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor formulate/adopt internal control measures/guidelines including sanctions therein for the proper management of collections and deposits. 

We have also recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:

all the collectors to prepare RCDs and remit cash collections daily to the Municipal Treasurer (MT); 


the MT to verify the RCDs submitted, make physical count of the accountable forms remaining in the custody of the collectors and check against the balances as reported in the collectors’ RCD to ensure that all collections are submitted;


deposit all collections and remittances received from collectors on the day it was received or at least on the next banking day; and


the Municipal Accountant to record financial transactions in the period to which they relate for accurate and reliable financial statements as required in Paragraph 27 of IPSAS I.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor: 

direct the Property and Accounting Units to update their respective records and, thereafter, compare and reconcile both records;

require the Municipal Accountant to draw the appropriate adjusting entries to correct the errors and misclassifications noted as well as transfer PPE under the Trust Fund books to the General Fund;


create a committee to prepare the policy on estimated useful life of PPEs of the Municipality for his approval;

create an Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory in three months or less and require the preparation of a Physical Inventory Plan (PIP) which shall be submitted to this Office at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory taking activities;

ensure that the Property and Accounting Units reconcile the inventory count per RPCPPE with the property and accounting records within ten (10) days from rendition of the RPCPPE by the Inventory Committee; and

ensure that annual inventory as of December 31 of each year be submitted to this Office not later than January 31 of the following year to facilitate the preparation and audit of financial statements.

We have recommended that Management:

a. require the officials preparing purchase requests and requests for price quotations to refrain from using brand names in the specifications of supplies and equipment to be procured;

b. publish in the PhilGEPS the Notice of Award, approved Contract, and Notice to Proceed;

c. effect payment of goods and services through check payable to the supplier/creditor except in cases where needed items are extremely necessary and urgent which cannot be conveniently paid by check; and

d. consider establishing a petty cash fund for payments of petty expenses of the Municipality.

