3.14. We have recommended and Management agreed to henceforth prepare and submit the report on RPCPPE within the required timeframe by considering the following:
3.14.1. Create an Inventory Committee to conduct a thorough physical inventory taking of all property owned by the municipality and prepare RPCPPE in the prescribed form;
3.14.2. Segregate destroyed/unserviceable and obsolete items found and noted during the count and report them in the Inventory and Inspection of Unserviceable Property;
3.14.3. Reassess the recorded unserviceable property and take the necessary actions for their immediate disposal in accordance with the rules on proper disposal; and
3.14.4. Require the reconciliation of records between the Property Cards and Subsidiary ledger cards to provide check and balance of accounting and property records.

4.12. We have recommended and Management agreed to strengthen its internal control on the submission, recording and deposit of collections by:
4.12.1. requiring the Municipal Treasurer to establish proper cut-off in the reporting of collections, particularly the daily accomplishment of the Report of Collections and Deposits by the Revenue Collection Clerks;
4.12.2. requiring the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that all RCDs turned-over by the RCCs are all recorded in the Summary of RCDs, and deposited on the date it was received;
4.12.3. requiring the Municipal Treasurer to supervise and monitor the RCCs on the reporting of issued accountable forms and submission of RCDs; and
4.12.4. strictly imposing administrative sanctions to erring Accountable Officers, when necessary.
